properties.name: camel.dataformat.any23.base-u-r-i
properties.description: The URI to use as base for building RDF entities if only relative paths are provided.

properties.name: camel.dataformat.any23.configuration
properties.description: Configurations for Apache Any23 as key-value pairs in order to customize the extraction process. The list of supported parameters can be found here. If not provided, a default configuration is used.

properties.name: camel.dataformat.any23.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable auto configuration of the any23 data format. This is enabled by default.

properties.name: camel.dataformat.any23.extractors
properties.description: List of Any23 extractors to be used in the unmarshal operation. A list of the available extractors can be found here here. If not provided, all the available extractors are used.

properties.name: camel.dataformat.any23.output-format
properties.description: What RDF syntax to unmarshal as, can be: NTRIPLES, TURTLE, NQUADS, RDFXML, JSONLD, RDFJSON, RDF4JMODEL. It is by default: RDF4JMODEL.
